metadata.name: Little Trees #62
metadata.description:
Delicate, little trees. Some with green leaves, some with orange, some with red. This is the genesis project of Brian Gawlik.

The default resolution is 3600x3600. To redraw and save as an image at a different resolution - in the live view, open your browser's devtools and execute the function saveImg(pixWidth) where pixWidth is the desired width in pixels of the image. For example, saveImg(4096) will prompt you to download a 4096x4096 image. It is recommended not to export below 2400x2400 as this will compromise the aesthetic of the shadow.

metadata.name: MEGASTRUCTURES #199
metadata.description:
MEGASTRUCTURES is a fully generative artwork. It renders a variety of space-age scenes, decaying megastructures left floating in space for centuries. 

It features:

- 4 Scenes
- 5 Star Colors
- 2 Star Positions
- 2 Star Sizes
- 3 levels of megastructure destruction / decay
- Special RAINBOW Variants


Megastructures can be plotted with the removal of occlusions using either illustrator or the occult vpype plugin. 

To save the piece as an SVG press any key. Note outputs may take some time depending on how powerful your device is.

metadata.name: CryptoPixels #828
metadata.description:
The ultimate collectible.
 
Traits? Well, each pixel has an R value, a G value, and a B value. And yeah, Tyler Hobbs, we know you’re reading and are about to say we should use H, S, and B instead but you can shove it up your ass right along with your Fidenza billions. Real deep up there.
 
Utility? With only 576 CryptoPixels you can make a CryptoPunk worth millions!
 
Rarity? Each pixel is provably unique (in the Heraclitean sense). And you know how one of your drunk crypto bros mentioned hashes once and it was the only word short enough for you to remember after blacking out? We give you 3 hashes. Think of the street cred with the even dumber fuckers out there buying random numbers!
 
Bullshit hidden messages? Oh yeah, you’re getting excited now, aren’t you? We’ve done some real alien shit and buried blueprints for a spaceship in here. You just have to work with the “community” to combine your pixels into the plans. Real. Fucking. Interstellar. Travel. How’s that roadmap?
 
Is this art? Are you art?

metadata.name: CA Panico #243
metadata.description:
Third chapter of the trilogy dedicated to Stephen Wolfram's cellular automata.
 
Compared to CA Vista and CA Monti, CA Panico aims to further abstract the concept of landscape using CA rules in a more massive way.

The great variety of CA rules that controls the coloring and textures, noise influence, division into quadrants, chance of having glitches and outages all combined with 25 palettes and 5 different formats means that the outputs will be very varied and peculiar.

Press 'S' to download, you can zoom downloaded output to enjoy all the details.

metadata.name: Gravures #256
metadata.description:
Gravures are digital paintings inspired by many influences. They recreating abstract nature using horizontal lines and a touch of randomness, resulting in a natural and organic appearance.

------------

In live mode :  
 - Press ’s’ to save a png - A4 (21 x 29.7cm) is the default size 
- Add an url parameter to choose between physical sizes (cm) : 20x30, 30x40, a4 or a3. 
At the end of the url you can add « &size=20x30 », « &size=a3 » …

metadata.name: Element #7
metadata.description:
Element is a generative series of pixelated mosaics that explores two contrasting styles of generative art. One style embraces imperfection and noise to simulate paint or other real-life textures, while the other produces digital outputs with precise forms.

The mosaics were inspired by the works of Hiroshi Kawano, one of the pioneers of generative art. They are generated by randomly placing rectangles inside a grid then applying a Markov-chain process multiple times. A hand-drawn and organic style is then incorporated using various techniques such drawing many rectangles with subtle variations in colour for a paint texture or adding different kinds of noise.

Please view in full-screen for the best experience.

Press [s] when the output is fully rendered to download it as a png file. The resolution can be set by adding for example "&s=2048" to the url for a 2048 x 2048 output.

Element was released as part of the Cure3 exhibition, generating vital funds for Cure Parkinson's medical research.

metadata.name: Bifurcation Rains #60
metadata.description:
When you look at the cityscape outside the window through the glass with the raindrops, it always seems to be undecided about its choice of state and position in space. It flows and wriggles, becoming fluid, half-river, half-thought-out fantasy. 
Bifurcation diagrams are visually similar to these traces left by water on glass. We have tried to imagine a moving world, which right now is at a point of choice.

Made with love, AI and p5.js code
To save the image, press the 's' key. Enjoy!

October, 2022
Julia V & YulikolaY
